Jakob Dylan is an American singer-songwriter born in 1969 in New York City to musician Bob Dylan and model Sara Lownds. He rose to fame as the lead singer and primary songwriter of the rock band The Wallflowers, writing hit songs such as "6th Avenue Heartache" and "One Headlight". More recently, he has released two solo albums in 2008 and 2010.
